WEBVTT 

﻿1
00:02:04.110 --> 00:02:08.030
Now. I'd say we stop off at
Juan Patròn's for one jolly big dram

2
00:02:08.239 --> 00:02:10.408
..and one ginger beer
with a dollar of whipped cream.

3
00:02:10.616 --> 00:02:11.909
Who gets the whiskey?

4
00:02:12.410 --> 00:02:15.537
Seniority. Doc. the one
closest to coffin. Anyway...

5
00:02:16.329 --> 00:02:20.250
If I buy you a dram. you must
promise not to tell the other boys.

6
00:02:20.500 --> 00:02:21.751
It's promised.

7
00:02:31.428 --> 00:02:34.264
Oh. no!
Not another hanging.

8
00:03:07.128 --> 00:03:08.129
Howdy.

9
00:03:08.838 --> 00:03:10.381
Come on lad.

10
00:03:12.675 --> 00:03:14.719
Hurry up. don't be afraid.

11
00:03:51.420 --> 00:03:53.089
You want to play games. pendejo?

12
00:03:53.297 --> 00:03:56.007
You red-assed Mexican greaser.
You do it with your horse!

13
00:03:57.592 --> 00:04:00.095
- Mexican greaser!
- Come here you little white chicken shit!

14
00:04:00.512 --> 00:04:01.763
Greaser! Greaser...
Come on greaser. cut me there!

15
00:04:01.972 --> 00:04:04.599
Hey. hey! Knock it off.
knock it off. hey!

16
00:04:04.808 --> 00:04:10.272
- Cut me there. Mexican!
- Hey! Knock it off! You know better. Chavez!

17
00:04:10.480 --> 00:04:13.024
- Navajo! Navajo!
- Enough!

18
00:04:15.277 --> 00:04:19.321
John's back. Now wash it up
and in your supper clothes! Now!

19
00:04:19.530 --> 00:04:20.739
Both of you!

20
00:04:28.664 --> 00:04:30.332
Who are them?

21
00:04:30.541 --> 00:04:33.877
"They". William. "Who are they?"

22
00:04:34.503 --> 00:04:36.754
They are the boys of the dregs...

23
00:04:36.963 --> 00:04:40.675
the flotsam and jetsam
of frontier society. if you will.

24
00:04:42.051 --> 00:04:44.762
We got room in the
bunkhouse. my young man.

25
00:04:45.013 --> 00:04:49.517
If you don't want to stay. the Santa Fe
runs out of Albuquerque in the morning.

26
00:04:50.351 --> 00:04:54.022
Glad you're back. Doc.
Stile hold the rope. inside.

27
00:04:54.230 --> 00:04:58.025
- John bring another hard case in?
- Hope it ain't another Mexican.

28
00:04:58.108 --> 00:04:59.484
Mexican-Indian.
you son-of-a-bitch!

29
00:04:59.985 --> 00:05:04.031
If you do wish to stay. well.
we have just the job for you.

30
00:05:09.745 --> 00:05:11.872
He ain't all there is he?

31
00:05:12.789 --> 00:05:13.749
Christ!

32
00:05:30.097 --> 00:05:32.934
Hey. did you know pigs
are as smart as dogs?

33
00:05:34.226 --> 00:05:35.228
It's true.

34
00:05:35.686 --> 00:05:40.023
I knew a fella in El Capitan...
taught his pig to bark at strangers.

35
00:05:43.193 --> 00:05:44.945
What you doing here. boy?

36
00:05:47.030 --> 00:05:49.491
We work for Mr. Tunstall as regulators.

37
00:05:49.699 --> 00:05:53.495
We regulate any stealing
of his property. We're damn good too.

38
00:05:54.996 --> 00:05:58.165
Mr. Tunstall's got a soft spot
for runaways. derelicts.

39
00:05:58.374 --> 00:06:02.378
vagrant types. But you
can't be any geek off the street.

40
00:06:02.586 --> 00:06:05.839
you gotta be handy with the steel.
if you know what I mean. earn your keep.

41
00:06:07.132 --> 00:06:08.634
Go on. go on. get!

42
00:06:08.968 --> 00:06:12.596
Not that I'm a pistoleer or
a knife smith like that greaser

43
00:06:12.805 --> 00:06:15.432
Chavez-Chavez. over there.

44
00:06:16.392 --> 00:06:18.018
I'm pugilist.

45
00:06:19.186 --> 00:06:22.314
But then I ain't expecting you
to know the explanation of that word.

46
00:06:22.815 --> 00:06:24.191
hog boy!

47
00:06:25.943 --> 00:06:27.903
Shit. you don't even know why I'm here.

48
00:06:28.112 --> 00:06:30.990
Sure I do. You're a runaway
derelict. scud bottom vagrant.

49
00:06:31.198 --> 00:06:33.701
ain't you. like the rest
of us. Footpad. maybe?

50
00:06:33.909 --> 00:06:36.662
Petty thief?
Rob a bank? Kill somebody?

51
00:06:40.248 --> 00:06:41.833
Kill somebody. huh?

52
00:06:45.169 --> 00:06:48.006
- Regulators!
- Hey. you ain't no regulator boy.

53
00:06:48.214 --> 00:06:50.174
you gotta stay here with the pork.
They're smarter than you anyway.

54
00:06:50.383 --> 00:06:51.426
You might learn something!

55
00:06:51.509 --> 00:06:54.345
Cattle looks spooked in the
lower forty. let's take a look.

56
00:06:55.763 --> 00:06:56.972
Smart ass!

57
00:07:02.269 --> 00:07:04.521
Well now. look at those appetites.

58
00:07:08.400 --> 00:07:11.612
William? Have some more.

59
00:07:15.198 --> 00:07:17.867
Have you ever
worked beef before. Billy?

60
00:07:18.701 --> 00:07:21.120
Yeah... I worked a little
out Fort Sumner way.

61
00:07:22.121 --> 00:07:25.124
Pete Maxwell's place.
Did the chow line.

62
00:07:26.208 --> 00:07:28.920
But. I got a way with cattle.

63
00:07:34.842 --> 00:07:37.344
What's so jolly funny.
Master Steven?

64
00:07:38.094 --> 00:07:40.263
That's no proper table manners.

65
00:07:42.724 --> 00:07:44.768
Got a way with hogs.

66
00:07:47.145 --> 00:07:49.105
Congratulations. Charles.

67
00:07:49.356 --> 00:07:52.359
You and Steven will be doing
the dirty crockery alone this evening.

68
00:07:55.028 --> 00:07:57.280
Sorry. John. it struck me funny.

69
00:07:57.655 --> 00:08:00.241
And to William. Both of you.

70
00:08:01.742 --> 00:08:05.371
Apologies William.
Just hacking on you. that's all.

71
00:08:05.996 --> 00:08:08.123
Yeah. we're just hacking on you.

72
00:08:16.090 --> 00:08:21.177
Rumor has it. you killed a man. Billy?
You don’t seem like the killing sort.

73
00:08:21.344 --> 00:08:23.471
Yeah Billy.
what'd you kill him for?

74
00:08:25.848 --> 00:08:28.017
He was hacking on me.

75
00:08:36.693 --> 00:08:44.866
"There are plenty of men...
who will never secede...

76
00:08:45.450 --> 00:08:47.202
"Succeed".

77
00:08:49.371 --> 00:08:53.041
"...Who will never
succeed anywhere."

78
00:08:53.250 --> 00:08:55.627
We got a whole roomful
of them right here.

79
00:08:58.379 --> 00:08:59.547
Well done.

80
00:09:02.633 --> 00:09:04.010
William.

81
00:09:09.348 --> 00:09:11.100
Yeah. sure.

82
00:09:11.475 --> 00:09:16.022
Well. excuse me. Billy...
Very sorry to offend you.

83
00:09:17.148 --> 00:09:20.609
But we're congregated here
to learn to read and write.

84
00:09:20.859 --> 00:09:23.153
You need more than
the skill with the firearm

85
00:09:23.236 --> 00:09:25.447
to succeed in the new world. Billy.

86
00:09:25.572 --> 00:09:27.282
So take up the journal

87
00:09:27.616 --> 00:09:30.327
and start where
the other boy left off.

88
00:09:30.577 --> 00:09:33.538
Or you can go straight back
to your home on the streets.

89
00:09:39.209 --> 00:09:42.046
"Young men who don't know
how to do any kind of business

90
00:09:42.129 --> 00:09:44.840
"and have no energy or application.

91
00:09:44.924 --> 00:09:47.301
"had better stay at a home
near their relatives

92
00:09:47.384 --> 00:09:49.178
"so they can be taken care of.

93
00:09:49.303 --> 00:09:52.056
"They are not wanted here
and will only come to grief

94
00:09:52.264 --> 00:09:56.018
"but men of enterprise
are practically sure of success."

95
00:09:57.645 --> 00:09:58.770
Splendid!

96
00:10:01.439 --> 00:10:05.610
A splendid reading. William!
Thank you.

97
00:10:05.944 --> 00:10:08.780
- Good-night gentlemen.
- Good-night Mr. Tunstall.

98
00:10:40.017 --> 00:10:41.269
Shit!

99
00:10:43.938 --> 00:10:45.064
Pig!

100
00:11:03.707 --> 00:11:06.293
- Good afternoon. gentlemen.
- Good afternoon. John.

101
00:11:06.710 --> 00:11:08.545
John. Mr. Dolan and Mr. Murphy here

102
00:11:08.628 --> 00:11:12.090
are complaining about their
merchandise wagon being plundered

103
00:11:12.507 --> 00:11:15.343
on several occasions
on their way into town.

104
00:11:15.844 --> 00:11:18.346
Quite frankly. John.
they think you're behind it.

105
00:11:18.555 --> 00:11:20.598
- That's a fargin' lie and you know it!
- Richard!

106
00:11:23.517 --> 00:11:27.980
Sheriff Brady. Mister Murphy
is going to continue coming to you

107
00:11:28.188 --> 00:11:30.900
claiming I've taken his property
until I'm pronounced a thief

108
00:11:31.108 --> 00:11:32.651
and shaken out of Lincoln.

109
00:11:33.527 --> 00:11:35.529
I've never touched his property.

110
00:11:36.530 --> 00:11:38.115
I have no cause.

111
00:11:39.574 --> 00:11:41.200
Well.

112
00:11:41.826 --> 00:11:45.204
the Belted Earl has spoken.

113
00:11:45.246 --> 00:11:49.626
Look behind you. Earl...
all I see are hired thieves.

114
00:11:49.834 --> 00:11:53.421
These boys are promising young
men acquiring an education.

115
00:11:53.630 --> 00:11:56.299
Well. I had you pegged
as the type that uh...

116
00:11:56.925 --> 00:11:58.468
that likes...

117
00:12:01.011 --> 00:12:03.639
educating young boys. Englishman.

118
00:12:09.811 --> 00:12:12.064
Rumor has it that you want
to be bidding against me

119
00:12:12.272 --> 00:12:14.691
for the government beef contracts.

120
00:12:15.525 --> 00:12:20.112
- It is just a rumor. isn't it?
- Lawrence.

121
00:12:20.363 --> 00:12:22.615
You have a beef outfit and a store.

122
00:12:23.407 --> 00:12:25.743
I have a beef outfit and a store.

123
00:12:26.244 --> 00:12:27.745
You're going to try to make money.

124
00:12:27.954 --> 00:12:31.791
I'm going to try to make money.
It's simple and it's fair.

125
00:12:34.377 --> 00:12:37.797
You see our good Sheriff
sitting up there on that horse?

126
00:12:38.256 --> 00:12:41.508
Do you know how much money
he's got invested in my store?

127
00:12:41.716 --> 00:12:44.135
His life savings. John.

128
00:12:44.678 --> 00:12:48.348
And it's not just Brady who
wants me to be getting those contracts.

129
00:12:49.099 --> 00:12:51.726
It's the Territorial District Attorney.

130
00:12:51.810 --> 00:12:54.854
the Chief Justice.
The U.S. District Attorney.

131
00:12:54.938 --> 00:12:56.773
The Santa Fe Ring.

132
00:12:58.567 --> 00:13:00.651
It's a family ring. John.

133
00:13:00.901 --> 00:13:04.363
And you don't come prancing in here
with your fat foreign capital

134
00:13:04.572 --> 00:13:06.824
and trying to change things.

135
00:13:07.324 --> 00:13:11.120
I made a very long steamship
journey from London. Mister Murphy

136
00:13:12.204 --> 00:13:16.000
So. I should be damned if I'm going
to be dissuaded... by something as ugly

137
00:13:16.208 --> 00:13:20.837
as political corruption.
So. I'd like you to take your threats

138
00:13:21.045 --> 00:13:23.798
and your sheriff
and get off my property!

139
00:13:24.007 --> 00:13:26.009
You are ambitious. Earl.

140
00:13:27.760 --> 00:13:31.973
But you'd be better off selling
ladies' undergarments in Hempstead.

141
00:13:34.684 --> 00:13:37.312
Alright men. that's enough.
Clear the way!

142
00:13:38.187 --> 00:13:39.564
This is a new country.

143
00:13:39.772 --> 00:13:42.983
We won't be bowing down
to you no more. Englishman.

144
00:13:44.735 --> 00:13:47.112
Get ready for hell!

145
00:13:53.035 --> 00:13:54.494
Back to work. chaps.

146
00:14:30.237 --> 00:14:32.989
Mr. Tunstall. my name's J. McCloskey.

147
00:14:33.198 --> 00:14:35.575
I heard you're having
some trouble finding help.

148
00:14:35.700 --> 00:14:36.868
McCloskey?

149
00:14:37.077 --> 00:14:38.662
You're one
of the Murphy's boys. aren't you?

150
00:14:38.870 --> 00:14:40.288
I used to be.

151
00:14:40.413 --> 00:14:43.959
He fired me.
I called him a fat sow.

152
00:14:44.334 --> 00:14:45.335
Did you?

153
00:14:47.504 --> 00:14:48.672
Lovely.

154
00:14:49.839 --> 00:14:51.967
The bunkhouse is over there.

155
00:16:04.493 --> 00:16:05.828
Regulators!

156
00:16:10.625 --> 00:16:11.792
Let's dance!

157
00:16:50.704 --> 00:16:54.166
- Look at that buddy go...
- He ain't all there. is he?

158
00:17:01.882 --> 00:17:03.883
Well. he's there enough
to be dancing with a pretty gal

159
00:17:04.092 --> 00:17:06.553
while we sit around here
pulling our tally whackers.

160
00:17:06.761 --> 00:17:08.346
Damn straight.

161
00:17:12.100 --> 00:17:14.060
We have to expose this Ring. Alex.

162
00:17:14.269 --> 00:17:16.938
Can you get me in
to see the Governor?

163
00:17:17.313 --> 00:17:20.608
Murphy's beat us to it.
And he brought the Governor

164
00:17:20.858 --> 00:17:23.443
a nice fat campaign contribution.

165
00:17:23.610 --> 00:17:26.238
They're tightening the yoke
on you. John. Of course.

166
00:17:26.446 --> 00:17:28.073
they want me out. too.

167
00:17:28.282 --> 00:17:31.869
They figure with me gone. no lawyer
would be crazy enough to represent you.

168
00:17:32.119 --> 00:17:34.454
You've heard of English
tenacity. haven't you?

169
00:17:35.289 --> 00:17:36.832
A toast to uh...

170
00:17:37.249 --> 00:17:39.877
enough grit to finish the last realm!

171
00:17:44.213 --> 00:17:48.342
Besides... if we gave in and left

172
00:17:49.552 --> 00:17:51.554
who'd look after my boys?

173
00:17:52.263 --> 00:17:55.266
Uh. medicine. Yes.

174
00:17:55.600 --> 00:17:59.228
I should receive my degree
from St. Michael's in July

175
00:17:59.395 --> 00:18:01.397
and then I should be
practicing here in Lincoln

176
00:18:01.564 --> 00:18:04.232
until my missionary to in the islands.

177
00:18:05.192 --> 00:18:06.776
How nice.

178
00:18:34.345 --> 00:18:37.181
Howdy. My name's Doc.

179
00:18:37.348 --> 00:18:39.225
What... what can I do
for you young man?

180
00:18:39.725 --> 00:18:42.311
Well sir. if you're an acquaintance
of the young miss

181
00:18:42.519 --> 00:18:45.897
I was wondering if I could entreat
the young lady to a dance?

182
00:18:46.189 --> 00:18:49.859
- Why. certainly.
- Thank you.

183
00:18:58.993 --> 00:19:01.621
- What's your name?
- Yen Sun.

184
00:19:02.288 --> 00:19:03.540
That's beautiful.

185
00:19:05.874 --> 00:19:09.878
- You're a friend of Mr. Murphy's?
- He is my guardian.

186
00:19:10.712 --> 00:19:11.630
How?

187
00:19:20.138 --> 00:19:23.933
- Hello there.
- Hello back... William Bonney. sir.

188
00:19:24.850 --> 00:19:26.811
Pat Garret. Pleasure.

189
00:19:27.895 --> 00:19:31.816
Excuse us. friend. We have
a request for the band.

190
00:19:35.319 --> 00:19:36.696
Pat Garrett!

191
00:19:44.244 --> 00:19:47.247
She'll love that I get
to be as big as him.

192
00:19:48.957 --> 00:19:52.752
No... bigger!

193
00:19:55.881 --> 00:19:59.050
So shows the snowy dove
trooping with crows

194
00:19:59.301 --> 00:20:02.679
As yonder lady
order her fellow's chose.

195
00:20:04.346 --> 00:20:08.017
- Pardon me?
- Uh... That's poem.

196
00:20:08.767 --> 00:20:11.687
I'm a poet. I wrote it.

197
00:20:12.354 --> 00:20:14.148
I'm sorry young man

198
00:20:14.398 --> 00:20:16.859
- but we must be getting along.
- We're getting along famously.

199
00:20:17.067 --> 00:20:20.112
- Thank you very much.
- I'm sorry I didn't recognize you.

200
00:20:20.196 --> 00:20:22.907
I was just informed that you're
part of the Tunstall company.

201
00:20:23.115 --> 00:20:24.033
Yes. I am.

202
00:20:25.200 --> 00:20:27.410
Then I'll be expecting
to see you follow

203
00:20:27.619 --> 00:20:30.580
your Englishman
out of Lincoln when he goes.

204
00:20:33.541 --> 00:20:34.709
You tell him...

205
00:20:35.418 --> 00:20:38.004
tell that slug to leave
no slime in the road behind him

206
00:20:38.213 --> 00:20:40.715
when he crawls back
to Wharf Street.

207
00:20:48.055 --> 00:20:53.310
- Hey. Alex! How you doing?
- Someone break up your dance. Doc?

208
00:20:53.519 --> 00:20:58.398
- Yeah... yeah. he's the girl's guardian.
- Guardian?

209
00:20:58.690 --> 00:21:01.527
- That's a gentle euphemism.
- Why?

210
00:21:01.735 --> 00:21:04.613
He had a shirt ruined
in the Silver City laundry.

211
00:21:04.862 --> 00:21:08.282
He took the celestial
woman's daughter as payment.

212
00:21:09.200 --> 00:21:10.618
- What?
- She's house entertainment.

213
00:21:10.826 --> 00:21:12.453
as I understand it.

214
00:21:13.996 --> 00:21:17.542
Come on. you can dance
with Susan. it's safer.

215
00:21:18.167 --> 00:21:19.252
Yeah.

216
00:21:36.268 --> 00:21:39.729
- Out of the way. mister.
- Ah. I do beg your pardon.

217
00:21:39.938 --> 00:21:45.068
- Alright. you and me.
- No. no. no. No it's "you and I".

218
00:21:46.026 --> 00:21:49.905
- Isn't that right John? "You and I"?
- Yes. yes. it is. it is.

219
00:21:56.161 --> 00:21:59.582
You and I.

220
00:22:26.148 --> 00:22:28.150
- Pugilist.
- He's something. ain't he?

221
00:22:28.358 --> 00:22:30.068
Happy New Year!

222
00:22:36.283 --> 00:22:39.453
- Happy New Year!
- Happy New Year!

223
00:23:47.434 --> 00:23:50.896
Go on Billy. Boys will be boys.

224
00:24:25.513 --> 00:24:28.348
No! No! It's too many!

225
00:24:30.309 --> 00:24:31.935
Get out of here!

226
00:24:48.201 --> 00:24:52.663
For as much as it hath pleased
Almighty God. in his wise providence.

227
00:24:52.872 --> 00:24:56.375
to take out of this world
the soul of our deceased brother.

228
00:24:56.792 --> 00:24:59.337
we therefore commit
his body to the ground.

229
00:25:00.171 --> 00:25:03.883
Ashes to ashes
and dust to dust.

230
00:25:05.676 --> 00:25:08.470
Murphy's henchmen
have to be brought in. J.P.

231
00:25:08.637 --> 00:25:11.348
I'm gonna take it to court
and bring Murphy down.

232
00:25:12.182 --> 00:25:14.726
- Have you talked to Sheriff Brady?
- Brady?

233
00:25:15.185 --> 00:25:18.563
Half of the murderers are members
of his posse. He won't touch him!

234
00:25:19.147 --> 00:25:20.649
You're the Justice
of the Peace. Wilson.

235
00:25:20.857 --> 00:25:23.818
You have the power to serve
warrants through special constables.

236
00:25:24.069 --> 00:25:28.280
What special constables? No one's fool
enough to going after Murphy's people.

237
00:25:30.824 --> 00:25:32.493
Deputize them.

238
00:25:33.035 --> 00:25:35.329
McSween. those are just boys.
Ain't one of them over twenty-one.

239
00:25:35.538 --> 00:25:37.915
Murphy's men will shred
them in half within a day.

240
00:25:38.123 --> 00:25:40.417
- Are you gonna deputize them?
- Hell no.

241
00:25:40.918 --> 00:25:42.837
No. I'm not. Alex.

242
00:25:44.839 --> 00:25:46.340
