00:49:03.587 --> 00:49:05.589
Doc. what are we gonna do?

487
00:49:05.798 --> 00:49:08.926
In a while it's gonna be crowded with
Murphy's men! Get the hell out of here!

488
00:49:09.092 --> 00:49:10.219
Come on Charley! Come on!

489
00:49:11.220 --> 00:49:15.265
Regulators!
Let's rock out! Now!

490
00:50:25.415 --> 00:50:29.169
- Where to. Doc?
- Going to Patricio if it looks safe.

491
00:50:29.794 --> 00:50:32.255
I gotta ride to
Dick's mother in Vermont.

492
00:50:32.881 --> 00:50:34.716
and get some clean wraps for this.

493
00:50:34.924 --> 00:50:37.135
Hey. whatever you do.
don't go near Lincoln.

494
00:50:37.635 --> 00:50:38.761
See ya.

495
00:51:02.366 --> 00:51:05.912
- What you doing there. Billy?
- Well sir.

496
00:51:07.330 --> 00:51:09.290
with the sight filed down

497
00:51:09.624 --> 00:51:13.544
I got an eighth of a second drop
on our good sheriff Brady.

498
00:51:18.216 --> 00:51:22.594
Billy. we can't touch the sheriff.
Dick said so. you know that.

499
00:51:23.136 --> 00:51:25.555
Besides. we can't keep this up.

500
00:51:25.931 --> 00:51:28.767
Yeah. Well. Dick
ain't around anymore. is he. Charley?

501
00:51:29.851 --> 00:51:31.770
And right now sheriff
Brady's in desperate need

502
00:51:31.978 --> 00:51:33.480
of being removed from office.

503
00:51:33.730 --> 00:51:38.443
We're not going after Brady.
nor Murphy men. no more.

504
00:51:39.653 --> 00:51:42.404
I told you I would find the way.
and the way is west.

505
00:51:42.530 --> 00:51:43.823
West. huh?

506
00:51:45.366 --> 00:51:47.368
West is that way.

507
00:51:48.285 --> 00:51:51.288
and the bastards we gotta kill
are that way.

508
00:51:51.539 --> 00:51:54.834
The only bastards who are gonna
get killed are us. chivato. Let it go.

509
00:51:55.042 --> 00:51:56.335
Let it go?

510
00:51:56.544 --> 00:51:59.380
Murphy's taking inventory
in Tunstall's store right now

511
00:51:59.505 --> 00:52:01.757
and you're saying
that means nothing to you?

512
00:52:06.761 --> 00:52:08.972
It means nothing to me?

513
00:52:11.766 --> 00:52:14.894
Murphy and his politicians
have taken more blood from me

514
00:52:15.103 --> 00:52:17.897
- than they ever will from you.
- Oh yeah?

515
00:52:18.106 --> 00:52:22.026
- How do you figure?
- The Red Sands Creek Reservation.

516
00:52:23.652 --> 00:52:26.029
- What's he talking about?
- I don't know.

517
00:52:26.238 --> 00:52:30.075
207 people butchered in the snow
with their stomachs empty.

518
00:52:31.368 --> 00:52:33.370
My mother's people.

519
00:52:35.122 --> 00:52:37.583
You see. Murphy and company
was under government contract

520
00:52:37.791 --> 00:52:40.627
to supply us with beef
and two winters ago

521
00:52:40.836 --> 00:52:44.213
he sent only rotten meat.
No corn. no flour.

522
00:52:44.422 --> 00:52:46.757
only rancid beef
crawling with worms.

523
00:52:46.966 --> 00:52:48.009
So I went out
with a band in the night

524
00:52:48.217 --> 00:52:50.094
to the traders' camp
to try and get food.

525
00:52:50.303 --> 00:52:52.638
Oh yeah. they welcomed us in.

526
00:52:53.139 --> 00:52:56.809
and then they opened fire on us.
I got away. only me.

527
00:52:58.019 --> 00:53:02.356
But when I got back to the Red Sands.
I found out that the army

528
00:53:02.565 --> 00:53:06.234
had already heard about
our big Indian uprising

529
00:53:06.443 --> 00:53:07.903
and they paid us back.

530
00:53:08.153 --> 00:53:12.157
My mother was cut by a saber
from her privates to her neck.

531
00:53:12.365 --> 00:53:14.284
My sisters were just babies

532
00:53:14.367 --> 00:53:16.912
and they had their heads
bashed in with boot heels

533
00:53:17.078 --> 00:53:19.581
so the army could save bullets.

534
00:53:19.998 --> 00:53:25.085
Everybody at my reservation
was butchered and it means nothing to me?

535
00:53:27.171 --> 00:53:28.589
Oh yeah.

536
00:53:28.798 --> 00:53:31.884
Yeah. I went to Lincoln
to take Murphy's head.

537
00:53:32.802 --> 00:53:35.679
And that's when
John Tunstall found me

538
00:53:36.639 --> 00:53:40.684
and he took me in.
and he taught me

539
00:53:41.060 --> 00:53:42.520
a better way to bury Murphy.

540
00:53:42.728 --> 00:53:45.855
Murphy buried him
the old Irish way. Chavez.

541
00:53:46.064 --> 00:53:47.857
That's right. Steve.

542
00:53:49.317 --> 00:53:51.736
And he starved out
your family. Chavez.

543
00:53:51.945 --> 00:53:54.948
And now he's doing it to every
small farmer in the territory.

544
00:53:56.574 --> 00:54:00.578
But if you wanna run go ahead.
Just go run on ahead.

545
00:54:01.079 --> 00:54:04.164
Bye.
You got no loyalty. Navajo.

546
00:54:04.373 --> 00:54:05.874
Navajo.

547
00:54:06.917 --> 00:54:09.795
Ain't nothing more than
a piece of chicken shit in the rain.

548
00:54:10.087 --> 00:54:11.630
No.

549
00:54:12.172 --> 00:54:15.551
We had our ceremony back
there on the ridge. chivato.

550
00:54:16.218 --> 00:54:19.179
Now. I don't know
what your vision told you.

551
00:54:19.263 --> 00:54:22.141
But my vision told me
we're headed for blood.

552
00:54:22.224 --> 00:54:23.517
Blood like a river.

553
00:54:23.724 --> 00:54:28.146
I'm the last of my clan.
the last of my people.

554
00:54:28.604 --> 00:54:31.858
If I die. and I am not
afraid of dying. chivato.

555
00:54:32.066 --> 00:54:34.485
the sacred hoop is broken.

556
00:54:35.987 --> 00:54:39.699
No. I have to go west
and make my people live again.

557
00:54:52.461 --> 00:54:56.047
Charley. you'll come with me?

558
00:55:02.888 --> 00:55:08.184
- You ain't gonna say much. dirty Steve?
- Cause he ain't got much to say. Charley.

559
00:55:09.018 --> 00:55:12.855
Or Steve understands the meaning
of the word "pals". don't you Steve?

560
00:55:13.522 --> 00:55:18.319
Cause if you got three or four good pals
well then you got yourself a tribe.

561
00:55:18.611 --> 00:55:21.113
There ain't nothing
stronger than that.

562
00:55:21.447 --> 00:55:23.657
We're your family now. Chavez.

563
00:55:24.657 --> 00:55:27.911
You walk away from us.
you break our sacred hoop.

564
00:55:29.621 --> 00:55:34.501
We gotta stick together. fellas.
It's the only way I see it.

565
00:56:32.264 --> 00:56:33.515
It's me. Doc.

566
00:56:37.269 --> 00:56:39.146
And that's our bet!

567
00:56:40.647 --> 00:56:41.731
I'll miss it!

568
00:56:42.107 --> 00:56:43.984
I know what you desire.

569
00:56:44.151 --> 00:56:47.279
You've come to lay with me
and cut me into tiny pieces with a knife.

570
00:56:47.362 --> 00:56:50.031
You're a bandit who eats
children and old people.

571
00:56:50.365 --> 00:56:53.660
I eat meat and potatoes.
Who told you that?

572
00:56:54.077 --> 00:56:55.579
My benefactor.

573
00:56:56.329 --> 00:57:00.000
Your benefactor?
That's the man that eats people

574
00:57:04.880 --> 00:57:08.507
Yen. if you want to stay here.
tell me now and I'll go.

575
00:57:09.884 --> 00:57:11.802
Do you wanna stay here?

576
00:57:14.847 --> 00:57:17.391
In China. girls are not necessary.

577
00:57:17.725 --> 00:57:20.811
When we have floods. fathers
let the girl babies wash by.

578
00:57:21.020 --> 00:57:24.648
- My benefactor has made me necessary.
- He's not made you necessary.

579
00:57:24.857 --> 00:57:27.025
he's made you a slave.

580
00:57:27.692 --> 00:57:29.569
I'm sorry.

581
00:57:31.279 --> 00:57:35.825
Necessary
is something you can't do without.

582
00:57:36.701 --> 00:57:39.204
I can't do without you.

583
00:57:42.332 --> 00:57:45.043
I keep the flowers
that you offered me

584
00:57:45.709 --> 00:57:51.340
in a little room... inside my head.
Inside my heart.

585
00:57:51.715 --> 00:57:54.426
Often. you come in
and you ask me to dance.

586
00:57:55.427 --> 00:57:57.137
I often say yes.

587
00:57:58.555 --> 00:58:01.183
I want to ask
something else of you now.

588
00:58:02.518 --> 00:58:04.812
I want you to go with me
to Roswell.

589
00:58:05.562 --> 00:58:07.438
There's a railroad
going to New York City.

590
00:58:08.022 --> 00:58:10.358
Two days we can be
on the train. We can be

591
00:58:10.566 --> 00:58:13.194
in another country.
In a city together.

592
00:58:16.531 --> 00:58:21.035
"The Bird".
by Josiah G. Scurlock. That's Doc.

593
00:58:21.661 --> 00:58:24.205
Once upon a midnight dreary

594
00:58:24.622 --> 00:58:28.041
as I pondered weak and weary.
they came knocking at my

595
00:58:30.210 --> 00:58:31.753
back porch.

596
00:58:33.505 --> 00:58:35.715
He ain't very original. is he?

597
00:58:39.010 --> 00:58:41.304
He been gone off a long time.

598
00:58:42.597 --> 00:58:45.767
I've been feeling he's gonna be
making a run for it.

599
00:58:47.935 --> 00:58:49.562
Who. Doc?

600
00:58:49.895 --> 00:58:53.023
Nah. Doc likes me.

601
00:58:53.232 --> 00:58:54.900
I can't stand him.

602
00:58:55.109 --> 00:58:58.112
He gets an idea in his head.
you can't get rid of it.

603
00:58:58.320 --> 00:59:00.406
If I stay with him much longer.
I'll be a stiff in a photograph.

604
00:59:00.614 --> 00:59:03.242
The only chance I have is
to get hell-bent for leather now!

605
00:59:03.451 --> 00:59:06.453
- They would chase us.
- I'm used to that.

606
00:59:08.747 --> 00:59:09.998
No.

607
00:59:10.874 --> 00:59:14.461
I'm unclean.
That is not for a young man.

608
00:59:14.669 --> 00:59:19.299
Yen. I used to ride with the dirty underwear
gang out of Liberty. Missouri.

609
00:59:19.591 --> 00:59:24.095
Then John Tunstall taught me that the past
is like an old yellow-back novel.

610
00:59:24.304 --> 00:59:28.307
When you're finished with it
you toss it out. you start a new one.

611
00:59:31.310 --> 00:59:32.561
Okay?

612
00:59:39.485 --> 00:59:41.612
You're necessary.

613
00:59:43.697 --> 00:59:44.740
No.

614
00:59:45.032 --> 00:59:46.699
- Go with me.
- No.

615
00:59:46.908 --> 00:59:49.327
- Come with me. Yen.
- Yen Sun?

616
00:59:52.371 --> 00:59:54.248
Yen Sun?

617
01:00:18.897 --> 01:00:20.148
Hey. Steve!

618
01:00:20.357 --> 01:00:22.484
- What?
- Doc's back!

619
01:00:22.692 --> 01:00:24.569
I told you he'd come back!

620
01:00:25.821 --> 01:00:27.488
Regulators!

621
01:00:27.863 --> 01:00:29.824
Let's saddle up!

622
01:00:30.908 --> 01:00:33.035
Sheriff Brady.

623
01:00:33.828 --> 01:00:36.038
we're gonna have
a lot of fun now.

624
01:00:45.172 --> 01:00:46.715
What the hell is he doing?

625
01:00:50.385 --> 01:00:52.220
He ain't all there. is he?

626
01:00:53.972 --> 01:00:55.473
Is he?

627
01:01:03.731 --> 01:01:05.859
Top of the morning to you. girls!

628
01:01:40.057 --> 01:01:42.852
Reap the whirlwind. sheriff Brady.

629
01:01:44.771 --> 01:01:46.272
Reap it.

630
01:01:49.858 --> 01:01:52.819
- It's for you. Alex.
- You weren't supposed to touch Brady!

631
01:01:53.028 --> 01:01:55.447
Sheriff Brady sent
the men who killed John.

632
01:01:55.655 --> 01:01:56.990
It was a good move for us. Alex.

633
01:01:57.074 --> 01:01:58.658
- Was it Billy?
- Yes it was!

634
01:01:58.867 --> 01:02:00.368
Have you seen 'The Independent'?

635
01:02:00.577 --> 01:02:02.829
The Governor's revoked
your deputation powers.

636
01:02:03.038 --> 01:02:04.790
You're now wanted
by the legitimate law

637
01:02:04.998 --> 01:02:06.750
as well as those outside the law.

638
01:02:06.958 --> 01:02:09.251
You're not only being hunted
by John Kinney and Murphy's men.

639
01:02:09.460 --> 01:02:10.920
You're being hunted by troops!

640
01:02:11.128 --> 01:02:13.089
Fort Stanton. Billy.
The U.S. Army!

641
01:02:13.297 --> 01:02:16.050
The government's put
a 200 dollar bounty on your head.

642
01:02:18.135 --> 01:02:21.388
You were supposed to serve
eleven warrants and expose the Ring.

643
01:02:21.472 --> 01:02:24.558
Instead you went out and you
went on the warpath... on a rampage!

644
01:02:24.642 --> 01:02:27.770
Now Richard's dead! And
we're living up here like fugitives!

645
01:02:28.020 --> 01:02:30.230
What the hell do you think
you're doing out there?

646
01:02:30.438 --> 01:02:31.981
I don't know.

647
01:02:33.149 --> 01:02:35.443
Maybe I'm trying to get some attention.

648
01:02:35.652 --> 01:02:38.363
Maybe I'm trying to get
President Hayes to look this way.

649
01:02:38.822 --> 01:02:40.198
They'll let Murphy and his bankers

650
01:02:40.407 --> 01:02:43.159
get away with anything
and I can't allow that!

651
01:02:43.410 --> 01:02:46.538
The more bastards I dust.
the more news stories they write.

652
01:02:46.788 --> 01:02:48.622
The more troops
they send out after us.

653
01:02:48.831 --> 01:02:50.916
the more President Hayes
is gonna have to raise an eyebrow.

654
01:02:51.125 --> 01:02:53.544
Come down and see for himself
what's going on here.

655
01:02:55.129 --> 01:02:58.006
Then he'll find out who's
really doing the killing.

656
01:03:03.846 --> 01:03:07.724
Alex? What are you gonna do?

657
01:03:09.642 --> 01:03:12.979
I'm gonna try to reach
the President myself... legally.

658
01:03:14.355 --> 01:03:17.191
It won't be easy to get past
the Governor. he's got so many.

659
01:03:17.400 --> 01:03:18.776
Yeah. I got plans for the Governor.

660
01:03:18.985 --> 01:03:21.779
Alex. what if you can't
get in touch with Hayes?

661
01:03:24.198 --> 01:03:26.993
I go back to Lincoln
and re-open John's store.

662
01:03:27.201 --> 01:03:29.703
Try to deal with that.
That's what John would want.

663
01:03:29.953 --> 01:03:31.621
We'll escort you.

664
01:03:32.414 --> 01:03:34.332
You'd be a death sentence
to anybody right now. Billy.

665
01:03:34.541 --> 01:03:36.084
I don't want your help.

666
01:03:36.960 --> 01:03:41.298
Alex. you didn't see
what they did to John.

667
01:03:42.758 --> 01:03:44.426
We did!

668
01:03:53.726 --> 01:03:55.269
Christ. Billy.

669
01:03:59.398 --> 01:04:01.358
Thank you. Billy.

670
01:04:01.650 --> 01:04:05.071
Billy. please
go to old Mexico. Please.

671
01:04:20.627 --> 01:04:22.712
Gentlemen. let's ride.

672
01:04:43.399 --> 01:04:46.318
- Alex...
- What the hell happened. Doc?

673
01:04:48.987 --> 01:04:50.822
There's a whirlwind out there.

674
01:04:53.366 --> 01:04:56.160
When you're in it. you can't get out.

675
01:04:56.285 --> 01:04:57.829
I'm sorry.

676
01:04:59.956 --> 01:05:03.709
I was wondering if you
remember that China doll?

677
01:05:04.127 --> 01:05:07.213
You know at the dance. fandango?

678
01:05:08.631 --> 01:05:11.592
I was sort of thinking that.
cause you're lawyer and all...

679
01:05:11.801 --> 01:05:13.803
maybe that there was
a legal way to...

680
01:05:14.011 --> 01:05:17.181
I don't even have enough ground
to stand on anymore. Doc. I mean it.

681
01:05:20.393 --> 01:05:22.478
Okay. yeah.

682
01:05:23.104 --> 01:05:26.190
Okay.
Thanks.

683
01:05:29.152 --> 01:05:32.362
Take care of yourself. Alex. okay?

684
01:05:41.580 --> 01:05:43.331
But what the hell's
the matter with him?

685
01:05:43.582 --> 01:05:46.835
I don't know. he's just belly-achin'

686
01:05:47.085 --> 01:05:50.504
about something or another
that he read in the newspaper.

687
01:05:51.297 --> 01:05:53.299
He got mighty spooked.

688
01:05:57.636 --> 01:05:59.680
Dirty Steve told me. Billy...

689
01:06:00.431 --> 01:06:02.391
told me what
they're writing in the papers.

690
01:06:02.600 --> 01:06:06.062
Steven told him about the party
sheriff Peppin's planning for us.

691
01:06:06.812 --> 01:06:10.940
- Party? Oh. you mean the hanging.
- Callate. chivato.

692
01:06:11.149 --> 01:06:13.234
Goddamn it. Billy?

693
01:06:14.527 --> 01:06:16.780
You've ever see a man hanged?

694
01:06:17.030 --> 01:06:20.408
His face turns flat purple...
and his eyes come up on him.

695
01:06:20.658 --> 01:06:24.412
Yeah. I seen Red Smitty hang.
Seen his head come clean off!

696
01:06:25.580 --> 01:06:27.290
It was a hell of a sight!

697
01:06:27.624 --> 01:06:29.834
I don't think Charley
wants to hear about Red Smitty.

698
01:06:30.043 --> 01:06:33.045
I think that what he'd like
to hear is that we're not going to hang.

699
01:06:34.588 --> 01:06:37.132
You mess your trousers they say.

700
01:06:37.674 --> 01:06:40.052
Gals watching and everything.

701
01:06:41.345 --> 01:06:44.765
If we get caught.
Charley. we're gonna hang.

702
01:06:47.601 --> 01:06:50.978
But there's many a slip
twixt the cup and the lip.

703
01:06:53.689 --> 01:06:56.526
We gotta do something
before they catch us.

704
01:06:58.653 --> 01:07:00.947
You all gotta let me do something.

705
01:07:02.615 --> 01:07:03.866
Okay. Charley.

706
01:07:33.978 --> 01:07:35.896
Damn Charley.
this is your last wish?

707
01:07:35.980 --> 01:07:38.607
Did your little carrot wet?
You could've done that back in Juarez!

708
01:07:38.816 --> 01:07:42.945
Some kind of a special woman.
Dirt Face. You'll understand that one day.

709
01:07:49.201 --> 01:07:53.455
Alright gentlemen. square up
and shell out for Bowdre.

710
01:07:56.082 --> 01:08:00.044
We'll be in the den.
Just yell if you need any help.

711
01:08:00.253 --> 01:08:02.297
You know
what to do. don't ya?

712
01:08:23.025 --> 01:08:26.612
- What's your name?
- Charley.

713
01:08:28.447 --> 01:08:30.240
Well. Charley.

714
01:08:31.283 --> 01:08:34.077
I don't remember you
but I guess you remember me.

715
01:08:34.327 --> 01:08:36.704
I meet so many young men
after the first.

716
01:08:36.871 --> 01:08:38.498
You know how it is.

717
01:08:40.208 --> 01:08:42.585
Why don't you
come over here. Charley?

718
01:08:46.547 --> 01:08:48.341
Hm. ma'am...

719
01:08:49.300 --> 01:08:51.386
I just wanna hold you.

720
01:08:54.638 --> 01:08:56.807
Whatever your pleasure. Charley.

721
01:08:57.557 --> 01:08:59.851
But it all cost the same.

722
01:09:25.918 --> 01:09:28.838
Darling when a man rides
200 miles to do a job

723
01:09:29.088 --> 01:09:32.632
you just bet your Spanish land grant
he's gonna get that job done.

724
01:09:34.384 --> 01:09:37.095
Now if this Billy the Kid's
around town like people say.

725
01:09:37.387 --> 01:09:40.473
he is 200 dollars
flat dead on this bar.

726
01:09:41.391 --> 01:09:44.102
You can't kill
what you can't catch.

727
